ease_region":{"id":5,"region":"japan"}},{"id":475956,"date":724636800,"human":"Dec 18, 1992","platform":{"id":29,"name":"Sega Mega Drive/Genesis"},"release_region":{"id":5,"region":"japan"}}],"screenshots":[{"id":442221,"image_id":"sc9h7x","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/sc9h7x.jpg"},{"id":473084,"image_id":"sca518","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/sca518.jpg"},{"id":473085,"image_id":"sca519","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/sca519.jpg"}],"similar_games":[19404,119156,13196,7615,111187,113201,27092,24426,28070,56967],"slug":"puyo-puyo","summary":"Puyo Puyo (1992) is an enhanced version of the 1991 MSX2 and Famicom Disk System game of the same name. The game was developed for the Sega System C-2 arcade hardware and ported to a variety of consoles.\n\nPuyo Puyo is a puzzle game in which the player matches four or more \"Puyo\" of the same color together. This game is the precursor to an identically-titled arcade release.\n\nPuyo Puyo contains three modes: Endless, Mission, and Verses. In Endless Mode, players match Puyo until the top of their well is filled. If the player chooses, either a giant 2x2 green Puyo or Carbucle will periodically help the player clear space on their board. Mission mode gives the player several challenges to complete, such as clearing a set amount of Puyo or clearing all Puyo of a certain color. Verses mode allows players to battle each other.","total_rating":65.29583069341864,"total_rating_count":13,"url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/puyo-puyo","videos":[{"id":89661,"video_id":"G48JMe7Y5Rw"}],"websites":[{"id":552061,"url":"https://puyopuyo.fandom.com/wiki/Puyo_Puyo_(1992)","type":{"id":2,"type":"Community Wiki"}},{"id":552062,"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Puyo_Puyo_(video_game)","type":{"id":3,"type":"Wikipedia"}},{"id":340877,"url":"https://www.twitch.tv/directory/game/Puyo%20Puyo","type":{"id":6,"type":"Twitch"}}]}